    <summary>Synchronizes qBittorrent's listening port with the port assigned by your VPN provider</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
## qbPortWeaver

qbPortWeaver is a lightweight Windows system tray application that automatically keeps qBittorrent's listening port in sync with the port assigned by your VPN provider.

### VPN Support

Works out of the box with **ProtonVPN** (log file), **Private Internet Access** (`piactl`), and any **NAT-PMP capable VPN or router** (RFC 6886). The provider is selectable from the Settings dialog.

### Port Sync

Runs on a configurable interval and updates qBittorrent's listening port via its Web API whenever the VPN-assigned port changes. Can restart qBittorrent after a port change to ensure it takes effect immediately, force-start it if it is not running, and optionally restart it if the connection drops. A fallback port can be applied when the VPN is disconnected.

### Visibility and Safety

The tray icon shows a color-coded status dot (green / orange / red) and the tooltip displays the current port at a glance. An interface mismatch warning alerts you if qBittorrent is not bound to the VPN adapter. A JSON status file is written after each sync cycle for external monitoring or scripting.

### Other Features

- Built-in log viewer with color-coded levels and live tail
- Post-update shell command hook for custom automation
- Automatic update checker against GitHub releases
- Optional auto-start with Windows

For full setup instructions and recommended VPN configuration, see the documentation at https://github.com/martsg666/qbPortWeaver#readme
    ]]></description>
